<main>
<structure po="poem"><structure l="line">
They say I have attachment disorder</structure><structure l="line">
from years in the orphanage-I say</structure><structure l="line">
I'm attached to dirt: to the grit</structure><structure l="line"> 
of stones, pulverized metal from</structure><structure l="line">
the slag heap, I learned touch</structure><structure l="line">
from air, I fashioned love from</structure><structure l="line">
strangers. Your families make no sense to me.</structure><structure l="line">
My mother's the 4 barrel of a 409,</structure><structure l="line">
my heart's dragstripped</structure><structure l="line">
from the shredded tires</structure><structure l="line">
of predators. Go ahead,</structure><structure l="line">
think of me-</structure><structure l="line">
throw the red flag down.</structure><structure l="line">
I'm one you never figured,</structure><structure l="line">
dead engine start on a quarter-mile strip,</structure><structure l="line">
my lo-jack is the split/</structure><structure l="line">
the pull away-</structure><structure l="line">
you back there,</structure><structure l="line">
    me running the distance.</structure></structure>


